{"id":"260819232_Controlling_the_Focus_of_Visual_Selective_Attention","abstract":"Selecting only a subset of the available sensory information before further detailed processing is crucial for efficient perception. In the visual modality, this selection is frequently implemented by suppressing information outside a spatially circumscribed region of the visual field, the so-called “focus of attention.” The model for the control of the focus of attention in primates presented here is based on a “Saliency Map” which is a topographic representation of the instantaneous saliency of the visual scene.","authors":["Ernst Niebur","Laurent Itti","Christof Koch"],"meta":["January 2002","DOI:10.1007/978-0-387-21703-1_6"],"references":["313705702_Components_of_visual_orienting","256083333_Preference_of_Personal_to_Extrapersonal_Space_in_a_Visuomotor_Task","246727904_Pyramid_Methods_in_Image_Processing","242919124_Independent_Attentional_Scanning_in_the_Separated_Hemispheres_of_Split-Brain_Patients","233813483_Orienting_of_attention","233398161_Texture-based_tasks_are_little_affected_by_a_second_task_which_requires_peripheral_or_central_attentive_fixation","227324826_Visual_selection_of_features_and_objects_Is_location_special_A_reinterpretation_of_Nissen's_1985_findings","225749272_Parallel_processing_of_park-whole_information_in_visual_search_tasks","225717479_Search_through_a_sequentially_presented_visual_display","225694083_Inhibition_of_return_to_object-based_and_environment-based_locations","225680308_Guided_Search_20_A_revised_model_of_visual_search","225562770_Vision_outside_the_focus_of_attention","220499689_How_Precise_is_Neuronal_Synchronization","22681368_A_two-stage_model_of_visual_search","21562166_Consequences_of_allocating_attention_to_locations_and_to_other_attributes","20769584_Detecting_conjunctions_of_color_and_form_in_parallel","20628103_Guided_Search_An_Alternative_to_the_Feature_Integration_Model_for_Visual_Search","292192425_Towards_a_Neurobiological_Theor